  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hip or knee arthroplasties allow a relief of pain and a good functional habilitative at
      patients suffering from degenerative osteoarthritis of these articulations with medium and
      long-term good results. The main objective of this study is to compare the efficiency in
      short and medium-term functional impact parlance of two surgical techniques:
      computer-assisted surgery and mini-invasive surgery compared to the conventional techniques
      thanks to an innovative technology of ambulatory analysis of walking.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
